HEADWORD: Upgather
<hw>Up*gath"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To gather up; to
contract; to draw together.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Himself he close <qex>upgathered</qex> more and more.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Upgaze</ent>⟦br⟧
